casebody.data:
Harris, Appellant, v. Pryor, Respondent. (Common Pleas of New York City and County,

General Term.

May 12, 1892.) Action by Henry G. Harris against S. Morris Pryer.

■ Argued before Bookstaver and Bischoff, JJ.

W. McMichael, for appellant. W. W. Hewitt, for respondent.

Ho opinion. Motion for reargument denied, with $10 costs. See 18 N. Y. Supp. 128.
